&lt;h2 id=&#34;impact-of-positive-point-distribution&#34;&gt;Impact of Positive Point Distribution
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;When positive points fail to adequately cover the crack region, incomplete edge recognition occurs, leading to a large number of incorrect segmentations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimization Recommendation&lt;/strong&gt;: The distribution of positive points should closely match the actual shape of the crack, ensuring complete coverage of the crack path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://whhong-research.github.io/p/sam%E8%A3%82%E7%BC%9D%E5%88%86%E5%89%B2%E5%AE%9E%E9%AA%8C%E6%8F%90%E7%A4%BA%E7%82%B9%E7%AD%96%E7%95%A5%E4%B8%8E%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD%E8%AF%84%E4%BC%B0/image-20250312104636392.png&#34;
