&lt;h3 id=&#34;problem-analysis&#34;&gt;Problem Analysis
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;After investigation, it was found that this issue is not isolated. Relevant GitHub Issue discussions are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/facebookresearch/segment-anything/issues/762&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;facebookresearch/segment-anything#762&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/facebookresearch/segment-anything/issues/620&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;facebookresearch/segment-anything#620&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/facebookresearch/segment-anything/issues/169&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;facebookresearch/segment-anything#169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Possible Causes&lt;/strong&gt;: The official demo may use different versions of model weights, post-processing optimizations, or additional inference strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;summary-and-recommendations&#34;&gt;Summary and Recommendations
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;key-findings&#34;&gt;Key Findings
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negative Point Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;: Reasonable use of negative points can effectively constrain SAM&amp;rsquo;s segmentation range and significantly improve crack identification accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Positive Point Distribution&lt;/strong&gt;: Positive points should fully cover the crack region and match the actual shape of the crack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sampling Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;: Skeleton-based directional sampling strategy outperforms random sampling and can generate more targeted negative points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Point Quantity Balance&lt;/strong&gt;: The number of prompt points should be moderate; too many will introduce noise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;practical-application-recommendations&#34;&gt;Practical Application Recommendations
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In crack segmentation tasks, it is recommended to adopt a combination strategy of &amp;ldquo;small number of positive points + appropriate number of negative points&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize using skeleton-based directional negative point sampling methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For complex crack morphologies, adopt a multi-point gradual refinement interaction approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pay attention to performance differences between local models and official demos, and perform post-processing optimization when necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;future-research-directions&#34;&gt;Future Research Directions
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore intelligent strategies for adaptive negative point quantity and position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Study optimal prompt point configurations for different crack types (horizontal/vertical/mesh)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Combine traditional image processing methods with SAM for hybrid segmentation strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
